Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
gui_report_trace_flightline(25.10)          gui_report_trace_flightline(25.10)

Name
       gui_report_trace_flightline  -  Saves information about the all flight-
       lines traced through the gui_trace_flightline command to the  specified
       file

Syntax
       gui_report_trace_flightline

       [-help]

       -file <report_name>

       Saves   information  about  the  all  flightlines  traced  through  the
       gui_trace_flightline command to the specified file.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description  of  the  gui_report_trace_flightline
              command.

              For  a detailed description of the command, use the man command:
              man gui_report_trace_flightline.

       -file <report_name>
              Specifies the name of the report file.

Example
       The following set of commands reports all traced flightlines:

       innovus            3>            gui_trace_flightline             -inst
       DTMF_INST/DMA_INST/present_state_reg_3  -sink -sink_level 2 -sink_color
       pink

       innovus      4>      gui_trace_flightline      -inst      DTMF_INST/RE-
       SULTS_CONV_INST/r852_reg_5 -sink -sink_level 2 -sink_color green

       innovus 5> gui_report_trace_flightline -file file1

       The tool saves the report as follows:

